<FIRST>r a PM-PuppyDelivery     10-12 0259</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Puppy Delivery,0269</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pizza Man Delivers Puppy After Car Runs Over Dog</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRAND ISLAND, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three sisters got an unexpected
delivery from the pizza man who had accidentally ran over the
family dog: a fluffy, white puppy to help make up for the loss.
   ``I was in tears,'' said the girls' mother, Julie Mendyk. ``I
couldn't believe he did something like that. It restored my faith
in young people.''
   Brett Croner, 20, accidently killed the first dog during a
Saturday night run for Pizza Hut.
   Croner said he knew how the girls felt because his own dog was
killed by a car last spring.
   ``To lose one is to lose a part of yourself,'' he said.
   Mrs. Mendyk said her daughters, Rachel, 8, Sara, 9, and
Jennifer, 12, were all smiles when Croner brought the new dog
Sunday afternoon.
   She said Croner had stopped and apologized to the family on the
night of the accident, but she told him it wasn't his fault because
the 3-year-old dog, Sandy, was chasing a cat.
   ``I've had people get more upset about me dropping a pizza than
me running over their dog,'' Croner said.
   Still, Croner said he was determined to help ease the girls'
pain. After looking at about eight or nine different pups, he found
a mixed-breed, female dog that looked like Sandy.
   He left the puppy at the door of the Mendyks' house with a note
that read, ``Please accept this puppy as my apology.''
   Mrs. Mendyk said the girls have named the 6-week-old dog Brett.
</TEXT>
