<SECOND>PM-BRF--Lost and Found,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Finds Stolen Jewelry Around Boy's Neck</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Phylis Robinson thought she would never
see the more than $9,000 in jewelry and other items stolen from her
home.
   But when Robinson, 35, took the bus to work Wednesday, she saw a
ring, gold nugget bracelet, gold watch and an 18-inch gold chain
she was sure were taken in Sunday's burglary. They were on a boy
riding near the back of the bus.
   ``It was on my mind that I might see somebody with the stuff,''
Robinson said. ``I couldn't believe it when I did.''
   She told the driver, who radioed the Rochester Transit System
dispatcher, who called police.
   Shawn Rucker, 16, of Rochester, was arrested and charged with
criminal possession of stolen property. He was being held Wednesday
night pending arraignment, police said.
   ``It was one in a million. The kid was shocked,'' said Sgt.
Louis D'Angelo.
   Robinson said the jewelry belonged to her and two friends who
live with her.
