<TEXT>
   The light illuminating the huge red
star atop parliament was switched off Thursday and will be removed,
the state news agency MTI reported.
   The announcement was preceded by a decision to gradually remove
the red star emblem from all public buildings and replace it with
national symbols.
   The removal of the red star from parliament would take place in
the first half of 1990 and will cost a considerable sum of money,
