<SECOND>AM-Israel, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0719,0446</SECOND>
<HEAD>Six Palestinians Die in Territories, One in South Lebanon</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 10 grafs UPDATING with two more deaths. Picks up
10th graf, Fellow Arabs ...</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By EILEEN ALT POWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli security forces killed four
Palestinians in the occupied territories Thursday and wounded 18,
including a 3-year-old whose skull was shattered, Arabs and the
army reported.
   The shrapnel-riddled body of another Palestinian was taken to
Ramallah hospital in the West Bank. Israel radio said he apparently
was killed while preparing a bomb.
   Nuhzu Mabruka, 35, was found hacked to death in an alley in the
Nablus central market. Arab reporters said she was killed because
she was a prostitute. Israel radio described her as a collaborator
with the Israelis.
   Military spokesmen said an Israeli patrol encountered
Palestinian guerrillas in south Lebanon before dawn and fired,
killing one. Army radio said the two other guerrillas in the group
escaped.
   Much of Thursday's violence occurred in Nablus, a West Bank town
that has been a center of rebellion during the 22-month-old
uprising against Israeli occupation.
   Arab journalists reported many confrontations between
Palestinians and soldiers. Hospital officials said 13 Arabs from
Nablus and nearby refugee camps were treated for gunshot wounds.
   Border police patrolling Jenin refugee camp fatally shot a
20-year-old man who tried to hurl a cement block down on them, the
army said.
   In the Gaza Strip, army gunfire reportedly killed one
Palestinian and wounded five. Doctors at Shifa Hospital said
3-year-old Atiyyah el-Ghurani of Shati refugee camp was hit in the
head by a rubber bullet that shattered his skull.
   Army spokesmen said the child was taken to Tel Hashomer Hospital
near Tel Aviv in critical condition and circumstances of the
shooting were being investigated.
   Israeli soldiers or civilians have slain at least 591
Palestinians since the uprising began on Dec. 8, 1987. Forty
Israelis have been killed.
   Fellow Arabs have killed 128 Palestinians, most of them on
suspicion of collaborating with Israeli authorities or for
prostitution or drug dealing.
   The encounter in south Lebanon took place in Israel's
self-declared security zone, near Markabe, a village 1{ miles north
of the border, the army said.
   Israel radio said the guerrillas had planned an ambush in the
security zone, which is patrolled by Israeli soldiers and a
surrogate militia of Lebanese Christians.
   Military sources said the dead man belonged to the Democratic
Front for the Liberation of Palestine, a Syrian-backed faction of
the Palestine Liberation Organization.
   The army said 71 guerrillas and two Israeli soldiers have been
killed in the border area this year.
</TEXT>
