<HEAD>List of 1989 Nobel Laureates</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS graf 3 `CHEMISTRY' to show that Altman is U.S. citizen.
Picks up graf 4 pvs, `PHYSICS ...'</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Nobels Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of the Nobel Prize
winners for 1989 announced so far:
   MEDICINE _ Americans J. Michael Bishop and Harold E. Varmus for
their discovery of a family of genes that has helped scientists
understand how cancer develops.
   CHEMISTRY _ American Thomas Cech and Canadian-born Sidney
Altman, a U.S. citizen since 1984, for their work with the genetic
material RNA.
   PHYSICS _ American Norman F. Ramsey for the atomic clock used as
the international time standard and American Hans G. Dehmelt and
West German Wolfgang Paul for a method to isolate single atoms.
   PEACE _ The Dalai Lama, the exiled spiritual and political
leader of Tibet, for his non-violent struggle to free his nation
from Chinese rule.
   ECONOMICS _ Norwegian Trygve Haavelmo for using statistics and
probability to forecast how economies behave.
   LITERATURE _ to be announced.
</TEXT>
