<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high East German official rejected the
democratic reforms some Soviet bloc allies have embraced and said
Thursday that communism will continue to dominate society.
   Another said the government will listen to ``all parts of the
population'' clamoring for change as long as they do not insist on
