curb inflationary pressures and maintain stability in foreign
exchange markets.
   Nevertheless, the dollar strengthened against the yen Wednesday
in Tokyo, continuing a recent rally that also has defied interest
rate hikes by European central banks.
   The Bank of Japan on Wednesday raised its discount rate, the fee
charged for commercial bank borrowings from the central bank, by
0.5 percentage point to 3.75 percent. The rate also affects other
interest rates in Japan.
