<HEAD>Seven-Year Treasury Note Yields Rose</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on seven-year Treasury notes rose in
Wednesday's auction to the highest level in six months.
   The average yield was 8.08 percent, up from 7.89 percent at the
last auction on July 12.
   It was the highest rate since an auction of seven-year notes
averaged 9.39 percent on April 12. The notes will carry a coupon
interest rate of 8 percent with each $10,000 in face value selling
for $9,957.90.
   A total of $7.5 billion in notes was sold out of bids totaling
$18.5 billion.
