<TEXT>
   Squibb Corp. President Jan Leschly resigned
Thursday to pursue ``opportunities outside the company,''
Bristol-Myers Squibb Co. announced.
   His resignation less than three months after Bristol-Myers
announced it would acquire Squibb in an $11 billion stock-swap deal
